text.section:
Except as provided in this section, before a person may harvest, cut, or otherwise remove or eradicate submerged aquatic vegetation from any land under the tidal waters of the State below the mean high tide, the person shall submit to the Department for approval a description of:
Why the removal of submerged aquatic vegetation is necessary;
The proposed method of removal;
A plan showing the site at which the activity is proposed; and
The extent of submerged aquatic vegetation to be removed.

section.section:
The plan under this subsection shall include the following requirements:
The name, address, and telephone number of the person making the request;
A written description by the person making the request of the reasons why it is necessary to remove the submerged aquatic vegetation;
The proposed method to remove the submerged aquatic vegetation; and
A diagram showing the location and extent of the submerged aquatic vegetation that is proposed to be removed.
